# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: WarriorPath | Scene: WarriorQueen7Hinterlands
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "In the days that followed, Sarah's army continued the march."
    new "In the days that followed, Sarah's army continued the march."

    old "The harsh winter of Rosanna proved true to its reputation, growing in intensity every day."
    new "The harsh winter of Rosanna proved true to its reputation, growing in intensity every day."

    old "A thick layer of snow slowed the march of her army as the wagons sank deeper into the unrelenting snow."
    new "A thick layer of snow slowed the march of her army as the wagons sank deeper into the unrelenting snow."

    old "The poor road, barely fit for a merchant's wagon, proved entirely insufficient for an army of her size."
    new "The poor road, barely fit for a merchant's wagon, proved entirely insufficient for an army of her size."

    old "As cold winds rolled in from the far western Hyral Mountains, they brought with them punishing hail and frigid temperatures."
    new "As cold winds rolled in from the far western Hyral Mountains, they brought with them punishing hail and frigid temperatures."

    old "Sarah watched the men of her army stumble through the fields, their heavy equipment slowing them down even further."
    new "Sarah watched the men of her army stumble through the fields, their heavy equipment slowing them down even further."

    old "Gathered around campfires at night, people sought out a warmth that lasted only briefly."
    new "Gathered around campfires at night, people sought out a warmth that lasted only briefly."

    old "During the day, their fingers and toes, their hands and feet, their limbs, their bodies, slowly gave into the cold."
    new "During the day, their fingers and toes, their hands and feet, their limbs, their bodies, slowly gave into the cold."

    old "The advancing frost mutilated those that underestimated it, turning hands cold and sickly blue."
    new "The advancing frost mutilated those that underestimated it, turning hands cold and sickly blue."

    old "As they pressed on, too committed to return, not all could endure the horror of the exposure."
    new "As they pressed on, too committed to return, not all could endure the horror of the exposure."

    old "After a few days, Sarah learned to spot them."
    new "After a few days, Sarah learned to spot them."

    old "The men that began to walk slower, stumble, sit and pause for longer than they should."
    new "The men that began to walk slower, stumble, sit and pause for longer than they should."

    old "The men that ceased to speak or to laugh, but marched like those already dead."
    new "The men that ceased to speak or to laugh, but marched like those already dead."

    old "Falling behind until they could move no more."
    new "Falling behind until they could move no more."

    old "They sat still by the side of the road, waiting for a death that seemed less horrid than the enduring suffering of the frost."
    new "They sat still by the side of the road, waiting for a death that seemed less horrid than the enduring suffering of the frost."

    old "On her orders, they did their best to bring these men into the medical carts, but some slipped through."
    new "On her orders, they did their best to bring these men into the medical carts, but some slipped through."

    old "Left behind to die to the frost, their bodies preserved until the spring."
    new "Left behind to die to the frost, their bodies preserved until the spring."

    old "Her army suffered the battering of the elements."
    new "Her army suffered the battering of the elements."

    old "But it endured."
    new "But it endured."

    old "By little over a week's march, they had finally made it through the Hinterlands."
    new "By little over a week's march, they had finally made it through the Hinterlands."

    old "They had survived the raids by the Tribesmen. They had survived the merciless frost. And now, she was rewarded."
    new "They had survived the raids by the Tribesmen. They had survived the merciless frost. And now, she was rewarded."

    old "Sarah, near the vanguard of her army, was one of the first to cross over the hill."
    new "Sarah, near the vanguard of her army, was one of the first to cross over the hill."

    old "And through the heavy snowfall, she saw the Capital of Rosanna, shining like a jewel through the cold dark."
    new "And through the heavy snowfall, she saw the Capital of Rosanna, shining like a jewel through the cold dark."

    old "Small fires, warming the homes of the people, shining out through their windows like a thousand tiny bonfires."
    new "Small fires, warming the homes of the people, shining out through their windows like a thousand tiny bonfires."

    old "Despite the torture and loss, Sarah smiled."
    new "Despite the torture and loss, Sarah smiled."

    old "Her army had made it."
    new "Her army had made it."

    old "She had made it."
    new "She had made it."

